      <section class="container py-14" id="faq">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 brand">FAQ</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold">How to install?</h3>
            <p>Get it from the Chrome Web Store and pin it. Then open an n8n editor page and toggle the assistant via the popup.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold">How does it use my data?</h3>
            <p>Prompts, optional images, and minimal page context (URL + visible errors) are sent to OpenAI solely to provide the requested functionality. We store only your settings locally.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Do I need my own OpenAI key?</h3>
            <p>Yes, for now. v2.0 will offer a freemium mode without your own key.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Is it free?</h3>
            <p>Yes, the Chrome extension is free. You pay only for your OpenAI usage (if any).</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Is it affiliated with n8n?</h3>
            <p>No. We are not affiliated with n8n GmbH.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
